id: pm-h4zb
title: Harden secret-scan guardrail for GitHub token prefixes and local credential hygiene
description: "A privacy re-audit confirmed the public shipping surface is clean and identified scanner coverage gaps for additional GitHub token prefixes plus a local-only ignored operations note that needed credential hygiene. The implementation broadened scanner coverage, made the rules unit-testable, and removed the local plaintext credential reference without tracking private operations details."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[5]: ci,dogfood,guardrail,privacy,security
created_at: "2026-05-20T20:19:27.785Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-21T18:16:35.461Z"
author: claude-code-agent
acceptance_criteria: Secret scanner detects all GitHub token prefixes (ghp_/gho_/ghu_/ghs_/ghr_/github_pat_); RULES + scanContent are exported and covered by a unit test; the scanner only auto-runs when invoked as a CLI; local-only credential material is removed from ignored operations notes; tracked secret scan remains clean; coverage stays 100%.
parent: pm-rnpb
resolution: Secret-scan guardrail now covers all GitHub token prefixes and is unit-tested; local-only credential material was removed from ignored operations notes.
expected_result: CI secret gate catches a wider class of GitHub tokens and the detection rules are regression-protected; no local plaintext credential material remains in ignored operations notes.
actual_result: Additional GitHub token prefixes are now detected; RULES/scanContent are exported and covered; local credential material was redacted from ignored operations notes; tracked security scan is clean.
files[2]{path,scope,note}:
  scripts/check-secrets.mjs,project,"broaden github-token rule to gh[opsru]_; export RULES+scanContent; guard run() to CLI-only invocation"
  tests/unit/check-secrets.spec.ts,project,"regression: all GitHub token prefixes + excludeFiles + clean-content negative cases"
tests[1]{command,path,scope,timeout_seconds,pm_context_mode,env_set,env_clear,shared_host_safe,assert_stdout_contains,assert_stdout_regex,assert_stderr_contains,assert_stderr_regex,assert_stdout_min_lines,assert_json_field_equals,assert_json_field_gte,note}:
  node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/check-secrets.spec.ts,null,project,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,secret-rule regression
close_reason: "Broadened the github-token rule in scripts/check-secrets.mjs from ghp_/github_pat_ to gh[opsru]_ (ghp/gho/ghu/ghs/ghr) + github_pat_. Refactored the scanner to export RULES and scanContent(file, content) and guarded run() behind a CLI-entry check (fileURLToPath(import.meta.url) === process.argv[1]) so importing it has no side effects. Added tests/unit/check-secrets.spec.ts covering all token prefixes, other high-risk shapes (private-key/aws/sentry-org/ssh-target), excludeFiles behavior, and clean-content negatives. Redacted the [redacted_local_ops_detail] from the gitignored [redacted_local_ops_detail] (replaced with a pointer to read from [redacted_local_ops_detail] / .env [redacted_local_ops_detail]); confirmed the literal exists nowhere else. pnpm security:scan passes 'No credential-like secrets detected in tracked files.'; new spec passes 5/5. scripts/ is excluded from the coverage allowlist so 100% coverage is unaffected."
body: ""
